The paper discusses a platform for collaborative management and integration of relational data, which suggests a focus on database systems (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a novel change propagation model that involves human intervention, which could fall under distributed computing (cs.DC) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper discusses potential harmful interference between updates and introduces notions of serializability, which suggests a focus on concurrency control (cs.SE) and possibly machine learning (cs.LG) for optimizing the algorithm.
